  "description": "The Rollin' 60s Neighborhood Crips are one of the largest Crip sets with ~1,600 members, formed in 1976 in Hyde Park, Los Angeles from the Westside Crips. Named after West 60th Street between Slauson and Florence Avenues. Described in 2004 as 'the largest black criminal street gang in the City of Los Angeles.' Members use Seattle Mariners and Chicago White Sox logos. Nipsey Hussle was a member (killed by a fellow member in 2019). In 2025, leader Eugene 'Big U' Henley Jr. was arrested for running a 'mafia-like' organization including kidnapping and murder. Rivals include Eight Tray Gangster Crips (feud started in 1979 over a girl) and Hoover Criminals.",
